        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-10-14T01:03:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I played around with a templatized function \n\ntemplate \u003ctypename T\u003e\nvoid set(const std::string\u0026 key, const T\u0026 value);\n\nThe problem I hit is that DiskSize is really just an int64_t, while we want to serialize it specially.\nI worked around it by using a single element POD-type struct for DiskSize instead of typedef\u0027ing.\n\nIt was fun while it lasted, but that seemed like unnecessary complexity added by the fact that this interface isn\u0027t trying to serialize types. (There isn\u0027t 1:1 mapping between the C++ types and the types in an ini file).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 89,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 89,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "3c2c56b6a225ba0ac507b7fb8f978a51786535f9",
